Sentence: There, Jack and Charlie Northrup, another prominent local gangster, get into a fight
Shortly after they leave, the news reaches their boat that Charlie Northrup's bloodstained car has been found in Brooklyn with one of Jack's men
Marcus learns that Northrup visited Jack one night
Jack was angry because Northrup had tipped off federal agents about one of Jack's rum boats, so Jack proposed a partnership as a means of allowing Northrup to pay him (Jack) back
Northrup refused, and Jack had his (Jack) men beat him (Jack) up
When Northrup fought back, The Goose shot and killed him (Jack)
